<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF107-914-470  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 914 470.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Personal Computing  Dec 1989 v13 n12 p111(4).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Software shortcuts to save time. (includes related article on tipsto speed up your applications)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Honan, Patrick.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Speed-enhancing, low-cost software such as a disk cache, MS-DOS'slatest versions, file recovery programs and keyboard acceleratorscan increase the value of older hardware.andP;  A disk cache is moreefficient in that it holds the most recently requested informationfrom the hard disk in RAM.andP;  Multisoft Corp's PC-Kwik PowerPakcosts $130 and is one of many available disk caches.andP;  BothFASTOPEN, DOS 3.0 and higher, and XCOPY, DOS 3.2 and higher, helpDOS load files faster by eliminating a step.andP;  SmartDrive, DOS 4.0and higher, helps buffers save even more time by caching completetracks of data into the buffers.andP;  Various commercial hard disk'housekeeping' programs which work at unfragmenting files areavailable, such as The Norton Utilities and Mace Utilities,available from Paul Mace Software for $99.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Multisoft Corp. (products)Paul Mace Software Inc. (products).andO;Product:   PC-Kwik Power Pak (Utility program) (usage)The Norton Utilities (Utility program) (usage)Mace Utilities (Utility program) (usage).andO;Topic:     SoftwareMSDOSDisk StorageCache MemoryHard Disk.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>